This paper is about developing malware detection methods for Android apps using similarity-based techniques. The paper focuses on using static binary features to detect malware, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The proposed methods also involve machine learning algorithms, which can be categorized under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the performance evaluation of the proposed methods, which can be categorized under software engineering (cs.SE) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
